-	Prepare post event evaluation and feedback report to the management and clients; 
-	Provide consultation and advisory to clients. Program Manager, Analyst & Public Relations Cisco Systems December 2012  –  December 2013  (1 year 1 month) Singapore I’m in charge of the Analyst Relations programs for APJC, often tying in with my global team and align to their global programs as well.  

I’ve had to develop and diligently execute on a yearly Analyst Relations strategy, focus and programs plan which includes events, briefings and activities for the year.  

I'm also involved in organizing both internal and external analyst-related events which my responsibilities would include, and not limited to, end-to-end event and budget planning, organization, analyst invitations and RSVPs, travel arrangements, on-site execution and post-event reports as well. Program Manager, APJC Collaboration Marketing Cisco Systems April 2011  –  December 2012  (1 year 9 months) Singapore During my tenure with the APJC Collaboration Marketing team, I’ve partake in developing our yearly and quarterly planning session and worked alongside my Marketing Manager(s) to develop, implement and execute marketing programs and campaigns with complete demand generation and lead nurturing activities across APJC for the Collaboration suite of products.  

I work closely with my global and regional marketing colleagues on developing and executing marketing campaigns, events and reporting for Partners and Customers in APJC and also maintaining the APJC marketing events calendar.  

Working closely with the various sales managers to develop and execute sales incentives programs for Partners – which includes developing the incentive mechanism, terms & conditions, tracking and fulfillment and also organize quarterly Webex sessions with Partners to provide updates on new incentive programs, offers & promotions, training etc.  

